cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving the performance of a permissioned blockchain system, which involves distributed computing and parallel processing. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as blockchain technology is closely related to cryptography and security. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper discusses the limitations of blockchain compared to established database systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as blockchain technology relies on network communication and protocols. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes architectural changes to improve the performance of Hyperledger Fabric.
